node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'things that don't make you a failure: @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic A relationship ending Not wanting the same things as everyone else •Changing your career Needing a break/rest Having others not validate your success'.

node.text: Let’s change the narrative around failing. Living life and making mistakes makes you human, not a failure ❤️ #millennialtherapist

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I'llmove ence they apologize @millennial.therapist/ millennial. Sara Kuburic Sometimes won't receive an apology that deserve. In those moments, will choose to validate my own feelings and give myself permission to close the chapter.'.

node.text:
I will not make my healing and growth dependent on someone else’s actions. 
#millennialtherapist #sorry

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'stop expecting yourself to: @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic Always be productive Never make mistakes Only feel positive feelings Be liked by everyone Learn things quickly Never change your mind'.

node.text: Make sure that the expectations you have set for yourself are realistic (and yours). #millennialtherapist

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Seeking control is often our attempt at regulating fear. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 26, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'when feeling upset, ask yourself: @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic What am upset about? What was the trigger? What is the narrative I've created surrounding this situation? What threat am perceiving? •What do need? What is my intention behind the way am acting right now? How can best take care of myself?'.

node.text: When upset, it’s important to pause and reflect (this is not always easy and may entail a lot of self soothing!). Checking in with ourselves is one of the best ways to allow us to discern what we need and which beliefs/past events might be feeding our current emotion. #millennialtherapist #feelings #human #instadaily #tips

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 25, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text: 👀 Yes, of course there are people out there that are selfish and/or have unrealistic expectations – but we also tent to attribute these labels to people who don’t deserve it  #millennialtherapist

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 25, 2021. May be an image of text.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Them: you're picky Me: am not picky. You just don't meet my standards. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'have the courage to: @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic Be yourself Want things that others don't Do what's best for you Say no Refuse to settle Expect your boundaries to be respected Distance yourself from toxic people Decline invitations Stand up for what you believe in Ask for what you want'.

node.text: It takes courage to be human. #millennialtherapist #courage #humanrights

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 23, 2021. May be an image of text.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'emotional boundaries can sound like: @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic "I am not ready to discuss this topic it's too personal" "When am upset, need some time alone" "I can't be your primary support system right now "I am still healing. need us to take things slow" "Violent movies make me uncomfortable, so I'll pass" "If you swear at me, this conversation will end" "I am not looking for advice, just need you to listen" "I need you to respect my privacy" am struggling"'.

node.text: Emotional boundaries often come with the difficult task of choosing *who* you want to share something with, *when* you want to share it, and *how* much you want to disclose. The purpose of emotional boundaries is to keep ourselves safe, ensure our emotional needs are met, AND nurture a meaningful connection with others #millennialtherapist #feelings

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"Idon'twant 'n their hurt @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic lam going to be honest, while being respectful and gentle about how present my truth. Lying does not honor the other person or my values.'.

node.text:
Having difficult conversations is a normal part of any relationship. We can’t control how someone will react, but we can ensure to approach difficult conversations with mindfulness and intention.

#millennialtherapist #truth #relationships

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '12 signs of growth @millennial therapist Sara Kuburic mistake Offering ourselves compassion when we make Taking responsibility for our actions and words Being intentional about setting and maintaining boundaries Being aware of what we need, think, and feel Actively working on accepting ourselves for who we are Striving to break detrimental patterns Validating our experiences and feelings Forgiving ourselves Trusting ourselves to make decisions Seeing our value outside of our output Treating ourselves with respect and kindness Giving ourselves permission to show up authentically'.

node.text:
Being human is hard, and our growth is not always linear or consistent. AND, remember, you’re not a project you need to fix. You’re a human that will make mistakes and learn along the way ❤️

#millennialtherapist #growth #tips

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Forcing things to fit your life will take away space from the things that are actually meant to be there. @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic'.

node.text: stop trying to force things that are not meant to be; make space for what is. #millennialtherapist #life #human #minimalist
